avy Field Artillery Group (Reserve), in Modena ([[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria c a 008.png|25px]] 8th Heavy Field Artillery Group \"Marmore\", in [[Modena]], ([[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt trasmissioni 43.png|25px]] 43rd Signal Battalion \"[[Abetone]]\", in Florence\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg trasporti 07.png|25px]] 7th Mixed Transport Battalion, in Florence\n** 27th Army Light Aviation Squadrons Group \"[[Mercury (planet)|Mercurio]]\", at [[Florence Airport, Peretola|Florence-Peretola Air Base]]\n*** 271st Light Airplanes Squadron ([[SIAI-Marchetti SM.1019|SM-1019]])\n*** 427th Recon Helicopters Squadron ([[Bell 206|AB-206]])\n\n==== Paratroopers Brigade \"Folgore\" ====\n* [[File:CoA of the Folgore Brigade.svg|30px]] \"'[[Folgore Parachute Brigade|Paratroopers Brigade \"Folgore\"]]\"', in [[Livorno]]\n** Command and Signal Unit \"Folgore\", in Livorno\n** [[Carabinieri Regiment \"Tuscania\"|1st Carabinieri Paratroopers Battalion]] \"[[Tuscania]]\", in Livorno\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt paracadutisti 187.png|25px]] 2nd Paratroopers Battalion \"[[Tarquinia]]\", in Livorno\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt paracadutisti 186.png|25px]] 5th Paratroopers Battalion \"[[Second Battle of El Alamein|El Alamein]]\", in [[Siena]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt paracadutisti 009.png|25px]] [[9th Parachute Assault Regiment|9th Paratroopers Assault Battalion]] \"[[Col Moschin]]\", in Livorno\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt artiglieria 185.png|25px]] [[185th Paratroopers Artillery Regiment \"Folgore\"|185th Paratroopers Field Artillery Group \"Viterbo\"]], in Livorno, ([[OTO Melara Mod 56|M56 105mm]] pack [[howitzer]]s)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA centro paracadutismo.png|25px]] Military Parachutist School, in [[Pisa]]\n*** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt paracadutisti 185.png|25px]] 3rd Paratroopers Training Battalion \"[[Operation Herring|Poggio Rusco]]\", in Pisa\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg logistico folgore.png|25px]] Paratroopers Logistic Battalion \"Folgore\", in Pisa\n** 26th Army Light Aviation Squadrons Group \"[[Jupiter|Giove]]\", at [[Pisa International Airport|Pisa-San Giusto Air Base]]\n*** 426th Multirole Helicopter Squadron ([[Bell 205|AB-205]])\n*** 526th Recon Helciopters Squadron ([[Bell 206|AB-206]])\n** Paratroopers Engineer Company \"Folgore\", in [[Lucca]]\n\n==== Motorized Brigade \"Friuli\" ====\n* [[File:CoA mil ITA mec bde Friuli.png|30px]] '''[[Friuli Air Assault Brigade|Motorized Brigade \"Friuli\"]]''', in [[Florence]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rpt comando e trasmissioni Friuli.png|25px]] Command and Signal Unit \"[[Friuli]]\", in Florence\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg corazzato 19.png|25px]] 19th Armored Battalion \"[[Gold Medal of Military Valor|M.O.]] Tumiati\", in Florence (two Leopard 1A2 tank companies and one VCC-2 mech infantry company)\n** 35th Motorized (Reserve) Infantry Battalion \"Pistoia\", in [[Pistoia]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 078.png|25px]] 78th Motorized Infantry Battalion \"Lupi di Toscana\", in [[Scandicci]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg fanteria 087.png|25px]] 87th Motorized Infantry Battalion \"[[Senio]]\", in Pistoia\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA rgt fanteria 225.png|25px]] 225th Infantry (Recruits Training) Battalion \"Arezzo\", in [[Arezzo]]\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA grp artiglieria 035.png|25px]] 35th Field Artillery Group \"[[Riolo Terme|Riolo]]\" in [[Pistoia]], (two batteries with [[M114 155 mm howitzer|M114 155mm]] towed [[howitzer]]s, one battery with [[OTO Melara Mod 56|M56 105mm]] pack [[howitzer]]s and one battery with [[FIM-92 Stinger|Stinger]] AA Missiles)\n** [[File:CoA mil ITA btg logistico friuli.png|25px]] Logistic Battalion \"Friuli\", in [[Coverciano, Florence|Coverciano]]\n** Anti-tank Company \"Friuli\", in Scandicci\n** Engineer Company \"Friuli\", in Florence\n\n=== Central Military Region ===\n* '''Central Military Region''' (R.M.C.), in [[Rome]], responsible for the regions [[Lazio]], 